This page have some redundant state with regards to handling signing state (can we sign? are we in process of signing? did the signing fail?). I want one way of dealing with errors and to know "have the handleSignClick method been called?". After click, if the sign URL isn't set (and the page location updated to navigate away), I want to have a spinner on the signing option, and disable the other buttons.

If errors happen, the state should be restored, so that customers can try an alternative form of signing.
I'll help you simplify the signing state management. Here's how we can refactor this to have clearer, more unified signing state handling:

